      "writtenOn": "2026-05-24T08:27:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is `fetch.autogc` intended to be a JGit-specific option? Native Git does not appear to document a `fetch.autogc` config key. Native Git has fetch CLI options `--[no-]auto-maintenance` / `--[no-]auto-gc`, while `receive.autogc` is documented specifically for receive-pack.\n\nSince `fetch.autogc` appears to be JGit-specific, should this use the JGit custom marker (\u0026#x20DE;) instead of ✅? The legend defines \u0026#x20DE; as \"JGit custom option not supported by native Git.\"\n\n```suggestion\n| `fetch.autogc`            | `true`  | \u0026#x20DE; | Perform an automatic garbage collection after the fetch operation has been completed.                                                               |\n```",
